Intrusion Detection and Attack indicators\par
What's the difference between an IDS and an IPS?\par
\b0 An IDS sends alerts based on a ruleset when traffic triggers those rules. But it does not act on it. \par
IPS will actively block and react to the rules it has been configured with to traffic on the network. \b\par
What's the difference between an Indicator of Attack and an Indicator of Compromise?\par
\b0 Indicator of Attack is when you are currently being attacked while an indicator of compromise is after you have been attacked. \b\par
